FT  30 JUL 94 / UK Company News: Tottenham buys Pounds 2m star
Tottenham Hotspur, the quoted north London football club, has announced its
second big acquisition in a week with the Pounds 2m purchase of Jurgen
Klinsmann, the German striker.
The deal follows negotiations between Mr Alan Sugar, the Tottenham chairman,
and the Monaco club where Klinsmann played until the end of last season.
Earlier this week the club agreed to pay Pounds 2.6m for Ilie Dumitrescu,
the Romanian striker.
Both deals will be financed from existing cash resources and banking
facilities.
